Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.12,0:00:20.74,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A sound mind gives rise to correct conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:22.87,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A calm tempo brings swifter truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.04,0:00:24.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Haibara and Mitsuhiko are in mortal danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:26.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Will you solve the "mushroom" message?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:28.75,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see one single truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.84,0:00:30.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I look like a child, but I have the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.84,0:00:32.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.71,0:01:45.88,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We Detective Boys decided to go mushroom\Npicking in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:50.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And during it, Genta got lost in the hunting area.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:55.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We split into two groups to search for Genta.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:01:57.30,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And Haibara and Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.14,0:02:02.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...discovered a dead body, and have become\Ntargets for the dangerous hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.56,0:02:10.61,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We found Genta, and three hunters decided\Nto help us look for Haibara and Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:18.99,Title,Sign,0,0,0,,Mushrooms, Bears, and the Detective Boys\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.82,0:02:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mushrooms, Bears, and the Detective Boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.91,0:02:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is our last chip.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.37,0:02:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have none left, Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.01,0:02:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.97,0:02:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were trying to escape, I twisted my ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.06,0:02:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was holding it in earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.40,0:02:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please let me see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.90,0:02:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.28,0:02:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, your foot is swelling and its purple!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.28,0:03:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll help you treat it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.08,0:03:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bear with it a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.58,0:03:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Treat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.16,0:03:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brought bandages?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.21,0:03:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, but I brought this towel and\Na pair of scissors. It'll be okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use the scissors and cut the towel like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! It became a long bandage!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.60,0:03:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you need to wrap it around the ankle twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.85,0:03:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from the bottom, you have to wrap it around to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.06,0:03:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you pull it tight here, and repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.27,0:03:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last thing you need to do is\Ntie the knot, and you're done!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.07,0:03:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, I sprained my ankle while we were\Ncamping before, and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.08,0:03:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.50,0:03:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} showed this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.30,0:03:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knows everything. He's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.01,0:04:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's also a great leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.68,0:04:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not even close to being like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The most important thing is that you know this\Nknowledge and can use it after learning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this moment, you're my outstanding rescuer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.66,0:04:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.21,0:04:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, n-no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm embarrassed by the way you said it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's dangerous staying here on this mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.72,0:04:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should go to the forest and think carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.76,0:04:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of a way to contact Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we should.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.33,0:05:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.58,0:05:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, near the place where you said, we discovered a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.71,0:05:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was covered with many branches and leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He died due to a gunshot to the abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.21,0:05:22.80,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ah, there was also the corpse of a cub buried nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cub?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.01,0:05:24.55,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:28.93,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The cub corpse was under a big boulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:31.18,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Anyway, this mountain is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:33.19,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Leave the search of the children to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.39,0:05:35.36,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You lot should start heading back now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.85,0:05:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.48,0:05:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cub!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.78,0:05:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought they found them, but it was only two cubs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.82,0:05:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The people in the hotel we're staying\Nat are helping us search!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.21,0:05:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the, you guys scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.42,0:05:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go after them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.38,0:05:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After sunset, it'll be difficult to search.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.05,0:06:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why didn't you tell them what really happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.01,0:06:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think one of those hunters might be the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.22,0:06:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not just "maybe."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, without a doubt, one of those three is the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.23,0:06:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He plans to kill Haibara and Mitsuhiko,\Nwho witnessed his murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.03,0:06:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why are they helping us look for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once both of them run out of places\Nto hide, the hunter will shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.54,0:06:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll just say he mistook them for a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you figured out who the culprit is, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.21,0:06:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.26,0:06:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't enough clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two will tell us who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll tell us in a way only we can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of mushrooms here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.74,0:07:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.45,0:07:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.87,0:07:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are three mushrooms on a branch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.87,0:07:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other four are scattered on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:19.50,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,Shiitake is another mushroom native to East Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the branch, from top to bottom, are\NTengutake, Matsutake, and Shiitake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:24.38,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,Shimeiji and Hatsutake are also only native to East Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the ground are three Shimeiji and one Hatsutake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.71,0:07:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, do those mushrooms mean something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.51,0:07:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.43,0:07:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, will they be able to figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.48,0:07:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's really interested in this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the secret code that we worked hard to think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.66,0:07:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.70,0:07:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like we don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.95,0:07:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those guys just really like to pick mushrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.96,0:08:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's keep going then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.71,0:08:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.05,0:08:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought there was a meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:09.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Professor, stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.64,0:08:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one looking for Haibara and Mitsuhiko,\Nthe identity of the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.94,0:08:20.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:24.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're going to fall asleep now, because\Nof this tranquilizer dart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, you're in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.36,0:08:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was aiming at the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.45,0:08:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.62,0:08:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because the murderer is one of those three!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.17,0:08:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how do you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though Haibara and Mitsuhiko were dropping potato chips everywhere, in order to show which way they went,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we never actually met up with them, and it\Nseems like they're still trying to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.97,0:08:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also, that hunter's corpse the police\Nfound near the cub's corpse...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.73,0:09:01.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Cub's corpse...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.40,0:09:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stun-gun wrist watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.78,0:09:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he has already figured\Nout our secret mushroom code.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.78,0:09:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like it, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.61,0:09:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, after he hits the culprit, we should take\Nthis cub and meet up with the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.45,0:09:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:34.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.51,0:09:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.52,0:09:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we stop playing tag, Mr. Murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.24,0:09:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can already tell, from the mushrooms, who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those seven mushrooms represent the seven of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.21,0:10:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scattered Shimeiji represent us three children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.42,0:10:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hatsutake is the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.71,0:10:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, the ones on the branch are Tengutake,\NMatsutake, and Shiitake,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which represent the three hunters and the\Nway they carry their guns on their backs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.56,0:10:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.64,0:10:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of the mushrooms on the branch, only\Nthe Tengutake is a poisonous mushroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.23,0:10:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the culprit is the person who\Nwears his gun on his right shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That's stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.78,0:10:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.32,0:10:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tengutake is a poisonous mushroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and anyone familiar with ths mountain would know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.95,0:10:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit found it before anyone else,\Nwouldn't he just destroy it right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.58,0:10:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, which is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.25,0:10:49.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, didn't I say it before?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.38,0:10:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were looking for mushrooms,\Nand pretended they were culprits.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.46,0:10:56.30,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Look, we found the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.68,0:10:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Matsutake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.14,0:11:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only we would know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.77,0:11:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.60,0:11:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the culprit the code hints at...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.52,0:11:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.45,0:11:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the culprit the code hints at is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.99,0:11:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saika Matasaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.88,0:11:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police have already found the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.34,0:11:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we don't have proof, the murdered\Nvictim was probably, skinny Uncle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your friend who came with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.97,0:11:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were committing your murder, Haibara and\NMitsuhiko came by coincidence, and found the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.35,0:11:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fired his gun at both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, Haibara thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If this goes on, he'll definitely end up killing us."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.41,0:12:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.74,0:12:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The opposition has a gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.49,0:12:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hurry up and use your stun-gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.00,0:12:09.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's aiming at something else...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.79,0:12:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.71,0:12:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this man was never going to kill Haibara and Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real reason this man fired his gun was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.69,0:12:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jubei!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.98,0:13:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you try to run away, the bear will\Ninstinctively think you're the prey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.36,0:13:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stare at her, and slowly back away from her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.74,0:13:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jubei! Do you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, calm your anger and return to the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.79,0:13:32.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to prepare food for the winter!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.83,0:13:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if you don't hurry and go, all the hibernation\Nplaces will be taken by other bears!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jubei, you need to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.26,0:13:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jubei...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara, the cub! Let the cub go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cub is probably Jubei's son! If he's near you, let him go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.48,0:13:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.37,0:14:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fired his gun to save\NHaibara, Mitsuhiko, and Jubei.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murdered hunter probably wanted to kill Jubei.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.06,0:14:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, trying to stop him, Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} shot the hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.31,0:14:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, Haibara and Mitsuhiko came.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before Jubei noticed both of them, he fired his gun\Nat them, in order to make them leave the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.66,0:14:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the tree beside the place where we found Mitsuhiko's badge there were bullet marks, probably made at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't he just shout to warn them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you may have noticed earlier, but\Nbears are actually very intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had yelled at them, it would have seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he fires his gun at them, both sides would get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.35,0:15:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.31,0:15:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we come here to hunt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.94,0:15:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something wrong with trying to kill a bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's also the ferocious beast this\Nold man always talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.87,0:15:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you the one that wounded that bear's eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.04,0:15:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.83,0:15:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jubei losing an eye was all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.09,0:15:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She exchanged one of her eyes to save my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.43,0:15:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-Exchanged?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.05,0:15:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That happened 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the spring season bear hunt, I came up this\Nmountain while it was still covered in snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.41,0:16:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had slipped while walking around the area, and\Nfell down 10 meters, breaking both of my legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.96,0:16:28.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under the state of my injury, I couldn't even speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.09,0:16:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when she appeared in front of my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.52,0:16:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I knew she was going to eat me,\Nso I closed my eyes waiting to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead, I felt something warm touch my cheeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.78,0:16:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was panicking, but when I opened my eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.95,0:16:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she was licking all of my wounds non-stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After she finished licking me, she slept next to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought she'd eat me when she woke up, but instead\Nshe used her black fur to cover me from the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could tell that she was really kind-hearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She eventually made me forget the pain in my legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.73,0:17:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I heard the sound of gunfire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had lost one of her eyes, and left my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.58,0:17:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The group of hunters had followed her footsteps,\Nand thought she was trying to eat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means if it wasn't for Jubei, they would never\Nhave found me, and I would have frozen to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:18:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, I went up the mountain everyday, found Jubei,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.18,0:18:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and made her go up the mountain\Nwhere no one would find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.32,0:18:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be that the legend of Jubei you told us was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.49,0:18:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.36,0:18:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a fake story I made up so that people\Nwould become afraid of Jubei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But recently, it seems to have had the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.67,0:18:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hunter is an animal lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.50,0:18:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for the murdered hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was hunting the bear, who was the enemy, but was\Nattacked by the hunter, who was supposed to be his ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.80,0:18:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bears are talented animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.85,0:18:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that the bears are enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only if they are unlucky, they will\Nbe seen and attacked by hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.81,0:18:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to stop that rash hunter. That man\Nwanted to hurt Jubei for no reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.36,0:18:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.62,0:18:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a cheap trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hunter probably used a cheap trick with the cub.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.67,0:19:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just as the boy says.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.46,0:19:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man wanted to kill Jubei so badly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that he killed one of Jubei's children!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.72,0:19:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung the corpse on a tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.31,0:19:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way that I see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,murdering a cub just to make its mother come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.03,0:19:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe that man was actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.57,0:19:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the only beast that was ever here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.37,0:19:48.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}One hour later, we met up with the police\Nthat were investigating on the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.54,0:19:51.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The old hunter was then taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.71,0:19:58.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He looked back at Jubei's mountain, with sad, lonely eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.72,0:21:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, the cub's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how you knew it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.94,0:21:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, I thought Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was trying\Nto track down Jubei and get rid of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.40,0:21:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never thought he would bury the\Ncub and make a tombstone for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.16,0:21:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even knew that Jubei had given birth to cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.16,0:21:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had many chances to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why didn't you hurry up and tell us earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.79,0:21:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I did, then Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would have\Nbeen arrested by the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.09,0:22:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Jubei would definitely have been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.34,0:22:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, how did you figure out that\NAi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was hiding with the cub?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were cub footprints on a lot of the\Nchips, so I knew they were together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.14,0:22:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} would often turn around and look behind us,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.94,0:22:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you knew the bear was following\Nthe cub's footprints, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bears often have two cubs in one birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.57,0:22:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cub found dead, and the one that was with Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My instinct told me that they were her children.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.83,0:22:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jubei was angry because her cub was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.87,0:22:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted to stop Jubei from attacking Haibara\Nand Mitsuhiko, who were with the other cub.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.38,0:22:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means that old man was more worried\Nabout the bear than us humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.93,0:22:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.18,0:22:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can't help that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To that Uncle, Jubei was a friend for 20 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.85,0:22:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.77,0:23:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When an animal lover goes this far, it's rather annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.19,0:23:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, b-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.57,0:23:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it great?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.36,0:23:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mother Bear was saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.12,0:23:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope they find a nice place in the forest to hibernate!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.95,0:23:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.09,0:23:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
